
I'm building a code about heavy machinery. In this code, I've used QSqlRelationalTableModel to relation with "machine table" dbtb_mkn. dbtb_mkn related with "dbtb_mkcins", "dbtb_mkmark", "dbtb_mkmodl" and "dbtb_clsn" tables. In "dbtb_mkn" table view (MKNtview) there are QComboBoxes which represent the related data fields. With QDataWidgetMapper i can synchronize the data fields. All comboboxes works fine in QTableView (MKNtview). I can add,change the comboboxes. And at the same time the model works fine (MKNmodel).
The Problem :
At the same time, i want to show all data fields in an other window. In this QWidget window, everything map, but only comboboxes can not synchronize with data fields. All comboboxes populate their contents correctly. But data can not write to the model (MKNmodel).   


/// main table
MKNmodel = new QSqlRelationalTableModel(this); 
MKNmodel->setEditStrategy(QSqlRelationalTableModel::OnFieldChange); 
MKNmodel->setTable("dbtb_mkn");
MKNmodel->setJoinMode(QSqlRelationalTableModel::LeftJoin);

/// relations
MKNmodel ->setRelation(MKNmodel->fieldIndex("mkn_cinsi"),
       QSqlRelation("dbtb_mkcins", "id_mkcins", "cinsi"));
cbxCinsiModel = new QSqlTableModel ;
cbxCinsiModel = MKNmodel->relationModel(
                      MKNmodel->fieldIndex("mkn_cinsi"));
MKNmodel ->select ();
/// the other relations are same

/// mapper MKN
mppMKN = new QDataWidgetMapper(this);
mppMKN ->setModel(MKNmodel);
mppMKN ->setItemDelegate(new QSqlRelationalDelegate(this));

/// combobox
cbx_mknCins = new QComboBox;
cbx_mknCins ->setModel(cbxCinsiModel);
cbx_mknCins ->setModelColumn(cbxCinsiModel->fieldIndex("cinsi"));


